The Vice President of the United States, Mike Pence, delivered remarks at Homeland Security Investigations in Houston, Texas, expressing gratitude and support for the men and women of U.S. Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE). Pence praised their efforts in making the country safer, highlighting their accomplishments in criminal arrests, removal of gang members, and seizure of drugs. He also acknowledged the challenges they face, particularly in Texas, due to the ongoing crisis on the southern border. Pence emphasized the need for Congress to act in closing loopholes in immigration laws and ending illegal immigration. He assured the ICE agents of the support and respect from the American people and offered prayers for their safety. Pence concluded by thanking them for their service and pledging to stay with them until the immigration system is fixed.